Honorable Minister of State for Petroleum Resources, Dr. Emmanuel Ibe Kachikwu was in attendance today as the Vice President of Nigeria, Professor Yemi Osinbajo SAN received the Chairman & Chief Executive Officer of Total, Patrick Pouyanné during a visit to the State House, Abuja. Dr. Kachikwu applauded Total’s presence in Nigeria while name-checking the innovative #Egina project. He adjured the Group to explore the need to build a Refinery in Nigeria so as to consolidate its presence in the downstream sector. Patrick Pouyanné in restating Total’s commitment to the long term development and the improvement of the lives of Nigerians through the provision of clean and affordable energy, reaffirmed total’s pledge to investments and continued play in the Nigerian Oil and Gas Sector. Tanimu is an Online Editor with Africa's Largest TV Network. Produces when not on Social media.